main event: Five airmen observed a round orange-colored object hovering and moving at high speeds near Ramore, Ontario on May 25, 1953.
interesting points: The object was first seen about 5 miles away and appeared stationary for about 10 minutes before moving and disappearing into the clouds., The airmen reported seeing the object oscillating as it moved closer., The object was described as being about 30 to 40 feet in diameter and emitted no sound., The five airmen considered reliable, all witnessed the object and confirmed its unusual behavior., The sighting lasted about 20-30 minutes with no physical evidence or photographs captured.
witness description: airmen returning to base after a trip
